{
  "question_id": "4f6ad885-d776-43fe-821c-8b32103a7b73",
  "short_text": "Hollow Pyramid",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print a **Hollow Pyramid** of `N` rows using stars (`*`).\r\n\r\n```\r\n   *\r\n  * *\r\n *   *\r\n* * * *\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `N` rows containing stars (`*`) as a **Hollow Pyramid** shown in the sample output.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 5`,\r\n\r\n- Print stars (`*`) on **5** rows as shown in the given image.\r\n\r\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-hollow-pyramid.png' widthPercent='70'/>\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nIn the given image,\r\n\r\n- The Empty box indicates a space (\" \").\r\n- The Star in the box indicates a star (\"*\").\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\nThe output should be,\r\n\r\n```\r\n    *\r\n   * *\r\n  *   *\r\n *     *\r\n* * * * *\r\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "24a05fee-1a95-4d78-b208-c3e715844f4c",
      "code_content": "n = int(input())\n\nfor row in range(1, n + 1):\n    left_spaces_count = n - row\n    left_spaces = \" \" * left_spaces_count\n    row_output = left_spaces + \"* \" * row\n    \n    if(row == 1 or row == n):\n        print(row_output)\n    else:\n        hollow_spaces_count = row - 2\n        hollow_spaces = \"  \" * hollow_spaces_count\n        row_output = left_spaces + \"* \" + hollow_spaces + \"* \"\n        print(row_output)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
